headline.main: Greek Privatization Agency Says Disused Airport Project to Go Ahead
headline.print_headline: Greek Privatization Agency Says Disused Airport Project to Go Ahead

lead_paragraph: A 7.9 billion euro plan to turn a derelict former Athens airport into one of Europe's biggest coastal resorts, included in Greece's latest international bailout, will go ahead despite recent delays, a senior privatization agency official said on Saturday.
